{"title_page": "Athletics at the 1980 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's high jump", "text_new": "{{Infobox Olympic event\n|event = Men's high jump\n|games = 1980 Summer\n|venue = [[Luzhniki Stadium|Lenin Stadium]]\n|dates = 31 July-1 August\n|competitors = 30\n|nations = 11\n|win_label = Winning height\n|win_value = 2.36 {{WR|athletics}}\n|longnames = yes\n|gold = [[Gerd Wessig]]\n|goldNOC = GDR\n|silver = [[Jacek Wszo\u0142a]]\n|silverNOC = POL\n|bronze = [[J\u00f6rg Freimuth]]\n|bronzeNOC = GDR\n|prev = [[Athletics at the 1976 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's high jump|1976]]\n|next  = [[Athletics at the 1984 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's high jump|1984]]\n}}\n{{AthleticsAt1980SummerOlympics}}\nThe '''[[High jump|Men's High Jump]]''' event at the [[Athletics at the 1980 Summer Olympics|1980 Summer Olympics]] in [[Moscow]], [[Soviet Union]] had an entry list of 30 competitors. The final was held on Friday 1 August 1980.<ref name=\"SR\">{{cite web |url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/summer/1980/ATH/mens-high-jump.html |title=Athletics at the 1980 Moscow Summer Games: Men's High Jump |accessdate=31 December 2017 |work=sports-reference.com}}</ref> Athletes absent due to the boycott included the West German [[Dietmar Mogenburg]], who had cleared 2.35 m in May 1980. \n\n==Medalists==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\" text-align:center; font-size:110%;\"  \n|-\n|{{OlympicGoldMedalist|[[Gerd Wessig]]|GDR|1980 Summer}}\n|-\n|{{OlympicSilverMedalist|[[Jacek Wszo\u0142a]]|POL|1980 Summer}}\n|-\n|{{OlympicBronzeMedalist|[[J\u00f6rg Freimuth]]|GDR|1980 Summer}}\n|}\n\n==Results==\n===Qualification===\n*Held on Thursday July 31, 1980\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n!Rank !! Group !! Name !! Nationality !! 2.05 !! 2.10 !! 2.15 !! 2.18 !! 2.21 !! Result !! Note\n|- bgcolor=ccffcc\n| 1 || B || align=left|[[Mark Naylor]] ||align=left| {{flagIOC|GBR|1980 Summer}} || \u2013 || o || o || o || '''o''' || '''2.21''' || Q\n|- bgcolor=ccffcc\n| 2 || A || al