 [[Stump Mitchell]]<br>\n51 - Brian Ruff<br>\n59 - Marc Buoniconti<br>\n66 - [[John Small (American football)|John Small]]\n\n==Future schedules==\n''This represents the most recent verified future non-conference games as of October 31, 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.citadelsports.com/news/2017/6/5/football-the-citadel-inks-home-and-homes-with-towson-elon.aspx|title=The Citadel Inks Home-And-Homes With Towson, Elon|publisher=The Citadel Bulldogs|accessdate=June 8, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.postandcourier.com/sports/citadel-football-sets-game-with-georgia-southern-for/article_7a3f374c-dd32-11e8-a0c8-8f253b351a03.html|newspaper=Post and Courier|location=Charleston, SC|title=Citadel Football Sets Game with Georgia Southern|date=October 31, 2018|accessdate=November 1, 2018|author=Jeff Hartsell}}</ref> The upcoming season schedule can be found at [[2018 The Citadel Bulldogs football team]].''\n''[[NCAA Division I FCS]] football teams are usually permitted to play 11 games per season.  In years when 13 weekends fall between Labor Day and Thanksgiving, they may add a twelfth game.  This will be the case in 2019, 2024, and 2025.  With nine football playing members, the [[Southern Conference]] regular season consists of eight games, leaving 3 non-conference games to be scheduled in most years.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.underdogdynasty.com/2016/6/12/11893096/ohio-valley-ovc-southland-ncaa-fcs-kickoff-12-twelve-games-labor-day|publisher=Underdog Dynasty|title=Ohio Valley and Southland Conferences Propose Permanent 12-Game FCS Slate|author=TK Maxwell|date=June 12, 2016|accessdate=August 29, 2017}}</ref>''\n{| class=\"class=\"toccolours\"\n|- style=\"{{CollegePrimaryStyle|Citadel Bulldogs|color=white}} text-align:center;\"\n! colspan=2| '''2020''' ||colspan=2| '''2021''' ||colspan=2| '''2022''' ||colspan=2| '''2023''' ||colspan=2| '''2024''' ||colspan=2| '''2025'''\n|- style=\"{{CollegePrimaryStyle|Citadel Bulldogs|color=white}} text-align:center;\"\