didates for ballot spots: Joe Sestak, Steve Bullock, Kamala Harris, Juli\u00e1n Castro, Marianne Williamson, Cory Booker, and John Delaney.<ref name=candidates>{{Cite web|url=https://ballotpedia.org/List_of_registered_2020_presidential_candidates|title=List of registered 2020 presidential candidates|website=Ballotpedia}}</ref> Three others dropped out after the New Hampshire primary. Since the beginning of the primary season, none of these other candidates have been awarded any delegates. \n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! colspan=\"2\" |'''Candidates'''\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em; text-align:center\"|[[Deval Patrick|Deval<br />Patrick]]\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em; text-align:center\"|[[Andrew Yang|Andrew<br />Yang]]\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em; text-align:center\"|[[Michael Bennet|Michael<br />Bennet]]\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em; text-align:center\" <!-- Delaney ----> |[[John Delaney (Maryland politician)|John<br />Delaney]]\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em; text-align:center\" <!-- Booker ----> |[[Cory Booker|Cory<br />Booker]]\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em; text-align:center\" <!-- Williamson ----> |[[Marianne Williamson|Marianne<br />Williamson]]\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em; text-align:center\" <!-- Castro ----> |[[Julian Castro|Julian<br />Castro]]\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em; text-align:center\" <!-- Harris ----> |[[Kamala Harris|Kamala<br />Harris]]\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em; text-align:center\" <!-- Bullock ----> |[[Steve Bullock (American politician)|Steve<br />Bullock]]\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em; text-align:center\" <!-- Sestak ----> |[[Joe Sestak|Joe<br />Sestak]]\n|-\n! colspan=\"2\" style=\"background:#eee; text-align:center;\" | Withdrawal date\n|<!-- Patrick -->Feb 12, 2020\n|<!-- Yang -->Feb 11, 2020\n|<!-- Bennet -->Feb 11, 2020\n| <!-- Delaney ----> Jan 31, 2020\n| <!-- Booker ----> Jan 13, 2020\n| <!-- Williamson ----> Jan 10, 2020\n| <!-- Castro ---->