s or Write-ins. Since the beginning of the primary season, none of these other candidates have been awarded any delegates. Of the over 200 people who have filed with the FEC as candidates for the Democratic nomination, the following have been placed on the ballot in at least one state.<ref name=\"candidates\" /> Since the beginning of the primary season, none of these other candidates have been awarded any delegates.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|- style=\"background:#e9e9e9;\"\n! colspan=\"7\" style=\"text-align:center; color:black\" | National popular vote totals for other candidates\n|- style=\"background:#eee;\"\n! style=\"width:150px; text-align:center; color:black;\"| Candidate\n! style=\"width:70px; text-align:center; color:black;\"| Votes\n! style=\"width:150px; text-align:center; color:black;\"| No. states on ballot\n|-\n|{{hs|**}}Uncommitted\u2020\n| 37,793 \n|<small>Various states</small>\n|-\n|{{hs|***}}Other\u2021<ref>{{cite web|author=Hadley Barndollar|url=https://www.seacoastonline.com/news/20200212/weird-write-ins-charles-manson-jesus-christ-get-votes-in-nh-primary |title=Weird write-ins: Charles Manson, Jesus Christ get votes in NH primary|publisher=seacoastonline.com|date=2020-02-12|accessdate=2020-03-02}}</ref>\n| 200\n|<small>Various states</small>\n|-\n|{{hs|De La Fuente}}Roque De La Fuente III\n| 13,438\n| 6 <small>(NH,UT,CA,AZ,CO,TX)</small>\n|-\n|{{hs|Ellinger}}Michael A. Ellinger\n| 3,463\n| 3 <small>(NH,AZ,CA)</small>\n|-\n|{{hs|Greenstein}}Mark Stewart Greenstein\n| 2,713\n| 3 <small>(NH,VT,CA)</small>\n|-\n|{{hs|Wells}}[[Robby Wells]]\n| 1,968\n| 5 <small>(NH,TX,MO,LA,CO)</small>\n|-\n|{{hs|Boyd}}Mosie Boyd\n| 1,773\n| 4 <small>(NH,UT,AR,CA)</small>\n|-\n|{{hs|Krichevsky}}Rita Krichevsky\n| 453\n| 2 <small>(NH,CO)</small>\n|-\n|{{hs|Haas}}Bill Haas\n| 382\n| 1 <small>(MO)</small>\n|-\n|{{hs|Hewes}}[[Henry Hewes (politician)|Henry Hewes]]\n| 311\n| 3 <small>(NH,AZ,MO)</small>\n|-\n|{{hs|Steinman}}Velma St