14 to 18, and was completed on February 22, 2020.\n{{excerpt|2020 Nevada Democratic caucuses|fragment=NVresults}}\n\n====South Carolina====\nThe South Carolina Democratic primary took place on February 29, 2020, three days prior to Super Tuesday.  \n{{excerpt|2020 South Carolina Democratic primary|fragment=SCresults}}\n\n===Super Tuesday===\n[[Super Tuesday]] took place on March 3, 2020.\n\n====Alabama====\n{{excerpt|2020 Alabama Democratic primary|fragment=ALresults}}\n\n====American Samoa====\n{{transcluded section|source=2020 United States presidential caucuses in American Samoa}}\n{{trim|{{#section-h:2020 United States presidential caucuses in American Samoa|Results}}}}\n\n====Arkansas====\n{{excerpt|2020 Arkansas Democratic primary|fragment=ARresults}}\n\n====California====\n{{transcluded section|source=2020 California Democratic primary}}\n{{trim|{{#section-h:2020 California Democratic primary|Results}}}}\n\n====Colorado====\n{{excerpt|2020 Colorado Democratic primary|fragment=COresults}}\n\n====Maine====\n{{excerpt|2020 Maine Democratic primary|fragment=MEresults}}\n\n====Massachusetts====\n{{excerpt|2020 Massachusetts Democratic primary|fragment=MAresults}}\n\n====Minnesota====\n{{excerpt|2020 Minnesota Democratic primary|fragment=MNresults}}\n\n====North Carolina====\n{{excerpt|2020 North Carolina Democratic primary|fragment=NCresults}}\n\n====Oklahoma====\n{{excerpt|2020 Oklahoma Democratic primary|fragment=OKresults}}\n\n====Tennessee====\n{{excerpt|2020 Tennessee Democratic primary|fragment=TNresults}}\n\n====Texas====\n{{excerpt|2020 Texas Democratic primary|fragment=TXresults}}\n\n====Utah====\n{{excerpt|2020 Utah Democratic primary|fragment=UTresults}}\n\n====Vermont====\n{{excerpt|2020 Vermont Democratic primary|fragment=VTresults}}\n\n====Virginia====\n{{excerpt|2020 Virginia Democratic primary|fragment=VAresults}}\n\n===Mid/Late-March===\n====Democrats Abroad====\n{{transcluded section|source=2020 Democrats Abroad primary}}\n{{trim|{{#section-h:2020 Democrats Abroad primary|Results}}}}\n\n====Idaho====\n{{transcluded section|source=2020 Idaho Democratic primary}}\n{{trim|{{#section-h:2020 Idaho Democratic primary|Results}}}}\n\n====Michigan====\n{{transcluded section|source=2020 Michigan Democratic primary}}\n{{trim|{{#section-h:2020 Michigan Democratic primary|Results}}}}\n\n====Mississippi====\n{{excerpt|2020 Mississippi Democratic primary|fragment=MSresults}}\n\n====Missouri====\n{{transcluded section|source=2020 Missouri Democratic primary}}\n{{trim|{{#section-h:2020 Missouri Democratic primary|Results}}}}\n\n====North Dakota====\n{{excerpt|2020 North Dakota Democratic caucuses|fragment=NDresults}}\n\n====Washington====\n{{excerpt|2020 Washington Democratic primary|fragment=WAresults}}\n\n====Northern Mariana Islands====\n{{transcluded section|source=2020 United States presidential caucuses in the Northern Mariana Islands}}\n{{trim|{{#section-h:2020 United States presidential caucuses in the Northern Mariana Islands|Results}}}}\n\n====Arizona====\n{{transcluded section|source=2020 Arizona Democratic primary}}\n{{trim|{{#section-h:2020 Arizona Democratic primary|Results}}}}\n\n====Florida====\n{{excerpt|2020 Florida Democratic primary|fragment=FLresults}}\n\n====Illinois====\n{{transcluded section|source=2020 Illinois Democratic primary}}\n{{trim|{{#section-h:2020 Illinois Democratic primary|Results}}}}\n\n===April===\n====Wisconsin====\n{{transcluded section|source=2020 Wisconsin Democratic primary}}\n{{trim|{{#section-h:2020 Wisconsin Democratic primary|Results}}}}\n\n====Alaska====\n{{excerpt|2020 Alaska Democratic primary|fragment=AKresults}}\n\n==Notes==\n{{notelist}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|refs=\n<ref name=\"GP\">{{cite web|title=Nevada Democratic Delegation 2020|url=https://www.thegreenpapers.com/P20/NV-D|publisher=The Green Papers|date=March 31, 2019|accessdate=April 12, 2019}}</ref> <!-- [[2020 Nevada Democratic caucuses#Procedure]] -->\n}}\n{{2020 Democratic primaries}}\n\n[[Category:2020 U